supportingDocuments.purpose.ProofOfCompa:
An official document that shows the address of the organization.
Acceptable documents:
- Recent water, electricity, or gas bill
- Official tax certificate or tax exemption certificate
- Proof of insurance document
- Property ownership document or a rental agreement
- Company domiciliation statement, if it is registered at the personal address of the legal representative

Acceptable documents:
- Latest Financial Statements / Annual accounts of the organization
- Copy of the document submitted to your tax office at the end of the last business period
- Latest accounting report to the General Assembly Meeting

Proof of income is a document or set of documents that demonstrates a person's income over a specific period of time.

supportingDocuments.purpose.SignedStatus:
Articles of association are a legal document that outlines the internal rules and regulations governing the management and operation of a company/Association. It is one of the key documents required when incorporating a company and serves as a constitution for the company. The articles of association typically include details such as the company's name, registered office address, purpose, shares and shareholder rights, board of directors, meetings and voting procedures, transfer of shares, and other rules and regulations governing the company's internal affairs. 

Acceptable documents:
- A signed and dated copy of the company article of associations
supportingDocuments.purpose.SwornStateme: Sworn statement for Ultimate Beneficial Owners

Please fill in the sworn statement attached declaring exactly how the company is structured and who owns more than 25% of the capital.

Please use the attached template.
supportingDocuments.purpose.UBODeclarati:
An Ultimate Beneficial Owner (UBO) certificate is a document that identifies and verifies the individuals who ultimately own or control a company or business entity.
UBOs are the individuals who have more than 25% of the company shares or voting rights. If there are none, the UBOs are the legal representatives of the organization.
supportingDocuments.purpose.UltimateBene: Proof of address for each beneficial owner
Identity document for each beneficial owner

Include one document for each person who owns at least 25% of the capital/rights to vote, or any person who controls your company's executive bodies or management.

Acceptable documents:
- Passport
- ID card (only applicable to citizens of member country of the EEE zone)
- Residence permit (only applicable to residents of member country of the EEE zone)
- Driver's license (only applicable to residents of a member country of the EEE zone)"
